  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe PR to avoid polling for sync committee duties (#2999) inadvertently introduced a minor bug that wasn't caught in review (my bad).\r\n\r\nBy skipping the duties run, no data is added to the `sync_duties` map, so the load here fails:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/c3a793fd73a3b11b130b82032904d39c952869e4/validator_client/src/sync_committee_service.rs#L157-L161\r\n\r\nThis manifests as repeated CRIT logs when starting a VC with no active validators:\r\n\r\n```\r\nMar 14 13:33:03.001 CRIT Failed to spawn sync contribution tasks, error: Error fetching duties for slot 3366763, service: sync_committee\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nWe could either:\r\n\r\n1. Gracefully handle the lack of data in sync_committee_service, logging a debug message, or\r\n2. Insert an empty value into the map from the sync committee duties service\r\n\r\nI think I prefer (1)\r\n\r\n## Workarounds\r\n\r\nThe CRIT messages will disappear once any of the VC's validators become active.",
